quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,And indeed We already brought Ibrahim (Abrahem) earlier his right-mindedness and We were Knowledgeable of him
  21,52,"As he said to his father and his people, \"What are these statues to which you are consecrating (yourselves)"
  21,53,"They said, \"We found our fathers worshiping them"
  21,54,"He said, \"Indeed you were already, you and your fathers, in evident error"
  21,55,"They said, \"Have you come to us with the Truth, or are you of the ones that play"
  21,56,"He said, \"No indeed, (but) your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth Who originated them, (2) and I am of the ones who testify to this"
  21,57,"And by Allah, indeed I will definitely plot against your idols after you have withdrawn, turning away"
  21,58,"So he made them into scraps, except a great one they had, that possibly they would return to it"
  21,59,"They said, \"Who has perfomed this with our gods? Surely he is indeed of the unjust"
  21,60,"They said, \"We heard a young man making mention of them; he is called Ibrahim.\" (Abraham)"
  21,61,"They said, \"Then come up with him (i.e., bring him) before the eyes of the multitude, that possibly they would testify"
  21,62,"They said, \"Is it you who performed this with our gods, O Ibrahim"
  21,63,"He said, \"No indeed, it was this great one of them that performed it; so, ask them in case they (can) pronounce (a word)"
  21,64,"So they returned one to another (Literally: returned to themselves) (and) then said, \"Surely you yourselves are the unjust"
  21,65,"Thereafter they were made to relapse (Literally: they were turned upon their heads) (into idolatry), (saying), \"Indeed you already know that these (can) in no way pronounce (a word)"
  21,66,"He said, \"Do you then worship, apart from Allah, that which does not profit you anything nor harms you"
  21,67,Fie upon you and upon whatever you worship apart from Allah! Do you then not consider
  21,68,"They said, \"Burn him away and vindicate your gods, in case you are performing that"
  21,69,"We said, \"O fire, be coolness and peace upon Ibrahim"
  21,70,And they would (devise) a plot against him; yet We made them the greatest losers
  21,71,And We safely delivered him and Lut (Lot) to the land We have blessed for the worlds
  21,72,"And We bestowed upon him Ibrahim and Yacuq?b, (Isaac and Jacob) (additional) gift (to him), and each (one) of them We made righteous"
  21,73,"And We made them Imams (i.e., leaders) guiding by Our Command, and We revealed to them the performance of charitable deeds, and keeping up the prayer, and the bringing of the Zakat; (i.e., payment of poor-dues) and they were worshipers of Us (alone)"
  21,74,"And Lut, (Lot) to him We brought judgment and knowledge, and We safely delivered him from the town that had been doing wicked deeds. Surely they were a woeful people, (and) immoral"
  21,75,And We caused him to enter into Our mercy; surely he (was) of the righteous
  21,76,"And Nuh, (Noah) as he called out (to Us) earlier, so We responded to him; then We safely delivered him and his family from the tremendous agony"
  21,77,"And We vindicated him against the people who cried lies to Our signs; surely they were woeful people, so We drowned them all together"
  21,78,"And Dawud (David) and Sulayman (Solomon) as they gave judgment concerning the tillage, as the sheep of the people roamed therein, and We were witnesses to their judgment"
  21,79,"So We made Sulayman to understand it, and to each We brought judgment and knowledge. And with Dawu?d We subjected the mountains to extol, and the birds; and We were Performers"
  21,80,"And We taught him the working out of clothing (i.e., coat of mail) for you to fortify you against your violence; then are you thankful"
  21,81,"And to Sulayman (Solomon) (We subjected) the wind, tempestuous, to run at his command to the land that We had blessed; and We were Knowledgeable of everything"
  21,82,"And of the Ash-Shayatin (The ever-vicious ones, i.e., the devils) (some) dived for him, and did lesser deeds (Or: other than that) than that; and We were their Preservers"